singhski 2025-04-03 12:00 p.m.
In the criminal matter of;
State of Mayflower v. sai138

Date of Judgement: 04/02/2025

The following parties appeared:
Prosecution: Funpark22
Defense: sai138, ajdude282

The State has charged the Defendant with:
Count One - 1 M.S.C. 2101 First-degree murder Count Two - 1 M.S.C. 7102 Discharging a Firearm in City Limits

The Court finds the Defendant guilty of:
1 M.S.C. 2101 First-degree murder

PLEA AGREEMENT
Both the prosecution and defense have agreed to a plea agreement. Within this agreement, the Defendant shall plead guilty to a single count of first-degree murder. In accordance with the plea agreement, the second charge of discharging a firearm in city limits was dismissed. The Defendant acknowledged that they waived their right to a trial, confront witnesses, and appeal with an exception for claims of ineffective assistance of counsel or prosecutorial misconduct. The State agrees that no additional charges arising from the same incident shall be made against the Defendant. The Court approves the plea agreement in full.

The Defendant shall serve a total of 45 minutes for the one count of first-degree murder.

/s/ Singhski
District Court Judge
